{
    "publish_date": "2013-08-27T15:04:52.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT3M20S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Without a doubt,", 
            "dur": "0.868", 
            "start": "6.547"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the most exciting scientific observation of 2012", 
            "dur": "2.759", 
            "start": "7.415"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "was the discovery of a new particle", 
            "dur": "1.913", 
            "start": "10.174"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at the CERN laboratory", 
            "dur": "1.06", 
            "start": "12.087"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that could be the Higgs boson,", 
            "dur": "2.059", 
            "start": "13.147"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a particle named after physicist Peter Higgs.", 
            "dur": "3.414", 
            "start": "15.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Higgs Field is thought to give mass", 
            "dur": "1.256", 
            "start": "18.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to fundamental, subatomic particles", 
            "dur": "1.716", 
            "start": "19.876"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like the quarks", 
            "dur": "0.879", 
            "start": "21.592"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and leptons", 
            "dur": "0.582", 
            "start": "22.471"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that make up ordinary matter.", 
            "dur": "1.902", 
            "start": "23.053"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Higgs bosons are wiggles in the field,", 
            "dur": "2.596", 
            "start": "24.955"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like the bump you see", 
            "dur": "0.884", 
            "start": "27.551"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when you twitch a rope.", 
            "dur": "1.502", 
            "start": "28.435"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But how does this field give mass to particles?", 
            "dur": "2.725", 
            "start": "29.937"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If this sounds confusing to you,", 
            "dur": "1.778", 
            "start": "32.662"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;re not alone.", 
            "dur": "1.242", 
            "start": "34.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In 1993, the British Science Minister", 
            "dur": "2.704", 
            "start": "35.682"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "challenged physicists to invent a simple way", 
            "dur": "2.329", 
            "start": "38.386"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to understand all this Higgs stuff.", 
            "dur": "2.013", 
            "start": "40.715"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The prize was a bottle of quality champagne.", 
            "dur": "2.464", 
            "start": "42.728"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The winning explanation went something like this:", 
            "dur": "2.618", 
            "start": "45.192"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Suppose there&#39;s a large cocktail party", 
            "dur": "1.888", 
            "start": "47.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at the CERN laboratory", 
            "dur": "1.032", 
            "start": "49.698"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "filled with particle physics researchers.", 
            "dur": "2.593", 
            "start": "50.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This crowd of physicists represents the Higgs field.", 
            "dur": "3.095", 
            "start": "53.323"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If a tax collector entered the party,", 
            "dur": "2.242", 
            "start": "56.418"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "nobody would want to talk to them,", 
            "dur": "1.348", 
            "start": "58.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and they could very easily cross the room", 
            "dur": "1.961", 
            "start": "60.008"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to get to the bar.", 
            "dur": "1.295", 
            "start": "61.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The tax collector wouldn&#39;t interact with the crowd", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "63.264"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in much the same way", 
            "dur": "1.304", 
            "start": "65.503"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that some particles don&#39;t interact with the Higgs field.", 
            "dur": "2.834", 
            "start": "66.807"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The particles that don&#39;t interact,", 
            "dur": "1.571", 
            "start": "69.641"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like photons for example,", 
            "dur": "1.685", 
            "start": "71.212"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are called massless.", 
            "dur": "1.544", 
            "start": "72.897"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, suppose that Peter Higgs entered the same room,", 
            "dur": "2.745", 
            "start": "74.441"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "perhaps in search of a pint.", 
            "dur": "1.844", 
            "start": "77.186"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In this case, the physicists", 
            "dur": "1.062", 
            "start": "79.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "will immediately crowd around Higgs", 
            "dur": "1.93", 
            "start": "80.092"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to discuss with him", 
            "dur": "1.133", 
            "start": "82.022"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their efforts to measure the properties", 
            "dur": "1.707", 
            "start": "83.155"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of his namesake boson.", 
            "dur": "1.704", 
            "start": "84.862"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because he interacts strongly with the crowd,", 
            "dur": "2.197", 
            "start": "86.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Higgs will move slowly across the room.", 
            "dur": "2.167", 
            "start": "88.763"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Continuing our analogy,", 
            "dur": "1.264", 
            "start": "90.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Higgs has become a massive particle", 
            "dur": "1.732", 
            "start": "92.194"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "through his interactions with the field.", 
            "dur": "2.113", 
            "start": "93.926"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, if that&#39;s the Higgs field,", 
            "dur": "1.909", 
            "start": "96.039"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how does the Higgs boson fit into all of this?", 
            "dur": "2.372", 
            "start": "97.948"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s pretend our crowd of party goers", 
            "dur": "1.857", 
            "start": "100.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is uniformly spread across the room.", 
            "dur": "2.375", 
            "start": "102.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now suppose someone pops their head in the door", 
            "dur": "2.405", 
            "start": "104.552"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to report a rumor of a discovery", 
            "dur": "1.385", 
            "start": "106.957"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at some distant, rival laboratory.", 
            "dur": "2.335", 
            "start": "108.342"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "People near the door will hear the rumor,", 
            "dur": "1.996", 
            "start": "110.677"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but people far away won&#39;t,", 
            "dur": "1.585", 
            "start": "112.673"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so they&#39;ll move closer to the door to ask.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "114.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This will create a clump in the crowd.", 
            "dur": "2.159", 
            "start": "116.138"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "As people have heard the rumor,", 
            "dur": "1.549", 
            "start": "118.297"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they will return to their original positions", 
            "dur": "1.412", 
            "start": "119.846"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to discuss its implications,", 
            "dur": "1.862", 
            "start": "121.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but people further away will then ask what&#39;s going on.", 
            "dur": "3.058", 
            "start": "123.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The result will be a clump in the crowd", 
            "dur": "1.889", 
            "start": "126.178"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that moves across the room.", 
            "dur": "1.691", 
            "start": "128.067"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This clump is analogous to the Higgs boson.", 
            "dur": "2.776", 
            "start": "129.758"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is important to remember", 
            "dur": "1.229", 
            "start": "132.534"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that it is not that massive particles", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "133.763"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "interact more with the Higgs field.", 
            "dur": "1.749", 
            "start": "135.623"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In our analogy of the party,", 
            "dur": "1.534", 
            "start": "137.372"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all particles are equal until they enter the room.", 
            "dur": "2.77", 
            "start": "138.906"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Both Peter Higgs and the tax collector have zero mass.", 
            "dur": "2.944", 
            "start": "141.676"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is the interaction with the crowd", 
            "dur": "1.892", 
            "start": "144.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that causes them to gain mass.", 
            "dur": "2.079", 
            "start": "146.512"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll say that again.", 
            "dur": "1.399", 
            "start": "148.591"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mass comes from interactions with a field.", 
            "dur": "3.046", 
            "start": "149.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, let&#39;s recap.", 
            "dur": "1.452", 
            "start": "153.036"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A particle gets more or less mass", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "154.488"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "depending on how it interacts with a field,", 
            "dur": "1.828", 
            "start": "156.298"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "just like different people will move through the crowd", 
            "dur": "2.132", 
            "start": "158.126"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at different speeds depending on their popularity.", 
            "dur": "3.682", 
            "start": "160.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the Higgs boson is just a clump in the field,", 
            "dur": "1.093", 
            "start": "163.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like a rumor crossing the room.", 
            "dur": "2.064", 
            "start": "165.033"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Of course, this analogy is just that --", 
            "dur": "1.848", 
            "start": "167.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an analogy,", 
            "dur": "1.22", 
            "start": "168.945"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but it&#39;s the best analogy", 
            "dur": "1.15", 
            "start": "170.165"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "anyone has come up with so far.", 
            "dur": "1.803", 
            "start": "171.315"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, that&#39;s it.", 
            "dur": "1.192", 
            "start": "173.118"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s what the Higgs Field", 
            "dur": "0.861", 
            "start": "174.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the Higgs boson is all about.", 
            "dur": "2.106", 
            "start": "175.171"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Continuing research will tell us if we found it,", 
            "dur": "2.141", 
            "start": "177.277"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the reward will probably be more", 
            "dur": "1.758", 
            "start": "179.418"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than just a bottle of champagne.", 
            "dur": "2.367", 
            "start": "181.176"
        }
    ], 
